  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global (Kenya, Liberia, Uganda, Mongolia and Tunisia): Pandemic Preparedness and Response: Strengthening National Legal and Policy Frameworks to Address Public Health Emergencies, Including COVID-19</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to contribute to the &#x2018;UN Framework for the immediate socio-economic response to COVID-19&#x2019;, by supporting countries in strengthening national legal and policy frameworks on preparedness and responses to public health emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To conduct a participatory gap analysis of the current national legal and policy frameworks in selected countries and develop a roadmap to legal and policy reforms needed to strengthen national pandemic preparedness and response. 2) Based on the findings of the participatory gap-analysis and roadmap, to support the development of technical assistance plans to define and guide IDLO&#x2019;s technical support to countries. 3) To deliver technical assistance and provide preliminary capacity development support to government and non-governmental stakeholders to enhance the necessary legal and policy reforms.</narrative>
  </description>
